Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} into 2cm wide wedges (peeling optional).

Pop the wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Spread out in a single layer. Roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}(trimmed) and quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%g}. Zest and quarter the @lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Mix the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with @oil{1%tbsp} (per 2P).

Pat the @salmon{200%g} dry with #kitchen paper{} then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Add the garlic, courgette and cherry tomatoes to a separate lined baking tray. Toss with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Place the salmon, skin-side down, alongside the veg and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Spread the @mayo{1%sachet} over the tops of the salmon fillets.

Spoon the breadcrumb mix onto each fillet. Press down firmly with the back of the #spoon{} to ensure it adheres.

Place the tray on the middle shelf of the oven.

Bake until the fish is cooked through and the breadcrumbs are golden, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, add @oil{1%tbsp} (per 2P), @sugar{1%tsp} (per 2P), the juice of two lemon wedges (per 2P), @mustard{1/2%sachet} (per 2P) and the lemon zest to a #bowl{}.

Mix well to make your drizzle.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Share the crispy potato wedges between plates.

Serve roast veg, crumbed salmon and remaining lemon wedges alongside.

Finish with a drizzle of the lemon mustard sauce.